The Japanese financial powerhouse has spent billions of Dollars buying shares in technology companies such as Amazon as it parks cash generated by a massive asset sale programme. The group has also made significant options purchases in tech companies, sources familiar with the matter told Reuters, in an aggressive bet by Chief Executive, Masayoshi Son on rising tech stocks. Options of $4 billion generated an exposure of about $50 billion, the Wall Street Journal reported. The group has made $4 billion in trading gains from those bets, the Financial Times reported. --Reuters--